title: Python in Excel - Beginner Tutorial
description:
üî• Learn Excel in just 2 hours: https://kevinstratvert.thinkific.com

In this step-by-step tutorial, learn how you can use Python in Microsoft Excel. If you've never heard of Python before, it's a powerful and popular programming language that has many libraries and packages that help you with data manipulation, statistical modeling, machine learning, and data visualization. By bringing Python into Excel, you now get all of these benefits directly in one place. We'll start with the absolute basics of how you even get started using Python in Excel and then we'll look at some of the additional power you get added on top of Excel.

üìö RESOURCES
- Sample Excel workbook to follow along: https://1drv.ms/x/s!AmxrofZZlZ-whapuySXkDuvEcSyusQ?e=Omtgd3
- CTRL + Alt + Shift + P to insert Python code
- CTRL + Shift + U to expand formula editor
- CTRL + Alt + Shift + M to toggle between Python object and Excel value
- Pandas documentation: http://pandas.pydata.org/docs/
- Bing Chat: https://www.bing.com/chat

‚åö TIMESTAMPS
00:00 Introduction
00:40 How to insert Python code
01:57 Multi-line editor
02:38 Hello World example
04:01 Assign value to variables
05:07 Reference variables
06:01 Row major order
07:42 xl function
09:10 Python output in Excel calculations
09:39 Calculation options
10:56 Python object vs. Excel value
13:39 Import data with Power Query
14:15 Libraries

19:32 Wrap up

title: Airboat Python Hunt: Went FULL SEND for This Giant Python
description:
Today we fired up the airboat and hit the Everglades looking for pythons. With the temps dropping, these snakes crawl out for some sun and that‚Äôs when we can catch them up sunning. We spotted gators everywhere, but when we finally saw that shimmer in the water, it was go time. Reo got his hands on his very first Burmese python. We threw him right into the action, and when that snake popped up, he didn‚Äôt hesitate for a second. There‚Äôs nothing like seeing someone get their first python.
